Vice President Kamala Harris met with President Hakainde Hichilema in Zambia to discuss their commitment to advancing democracy globally. Harris announced new democracy programs to promote anti-corruption, governance reforms, and financial transparency in Zambia. They also discussed signing a Commercial Development Memorandum of Understanding to boost commercial engagement. Harris expressed the United States' commitment to Zambia's economic revitalization and debt reduction, as well as cooperation at the United Nations and in the Southern African Development Community.